byline.original: By ASHLEY PARKER and JEFF ZELENY

abstract: Republican presidential candidate Mitt Romney returns to Iowa to campaign after refusing to signal his intentions about the state; the move makes it clear that Romney is not ceding the state to any of his rivals.
snippet: After months of refusing to signal his intentions for Iowa, Mr. Romney visited the state, making clear that he is not ceding it to any of his rivals.
lead_paragraph: After months of refusing to signal his intentions for Iowa, Mr. Romney visited the state, making clear that he is not ceding it to any of his rivals.

headline.main: Romney Will Compete in Iowa, if a Bit Cautiously
headline.print_headline: Romney Will Compete in Iowa, if a Bit Cautiously
headline.seo: Romney Visits Iowa and Says He Hopes to Win Caucus
